mods_title_ms: Photograph of 3rd page of Los Angeles Times Sunday Magazine story about Drum Barracks, "When Camels Carried Mail to California," by Basil Heathcote, 1930
dc.description: Text from nitrate negative sleeve: 1823 - 1824 253R1694 2 negs, 1929.  Photo by Adelbert Bartlett, 535 15th Street, Santa Monica, Calif.  Drum Barracks, 1862-68, offcers qtrs. U.S. Army, Wilmington (now in Los Angeles at L.A. Harbor) Calif. (see story attached)
Access to this collection is generously supported by Arcadia funds.
Drum Barracks story is only partially visible, in folded upside-down section of text at top.  Main story on page is "The Miniature Theater Magnate," by Mayfield Allen.

Text reads in part: ... soldiers were sent from Drum Barracks to Catalina Island, where new barracks were erected and garrisoned for awhile, after which the men were ordered back to their regular posts. ...
